<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
The level or intensity of a signal sent from a <a title="videodisc" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/videodisc">videodisc</a> player to a monitor during the <a title="Blanking Interval" href="Blanking_Interval">blanking interval</a>, usually zero, resulting in a blank screen. <em>Blanking level</em> also refers to the intensity of the signal during the <a title="Horizontal Blanking Interval" href="Horizontal_Blanking_Interval">horizontal blanking interval</a> and <a title="Vertical Blanking Interval" href="Vertical_Blanking_Interval">vertical blanking interval</a>, which needs to always be zero, or no signal, so as to prevent distortion of the screen by the electron gun. 
</p>
